\ Polymorphic unary math on a variable read inside a definition must match the
\ top-level result. The compile-time fuser sees `var op` and may emit a fused
\ superword; that must never change what the tag-checked words compute for
\ matrix or quantity operands.

variable mat   [ 1 4 9 16 ] 2 2 matrix to mat
variable dur   3 s to dur
variable x     2.25 to x

: mat-sqrt   mat sqrt ;
: mat-exp    mat exp ;
: mat-sin    mat sin ;
: mat-round  mat round ;
: dur-neg    dur negate ;
: dur-abs    dur negate abs ;
: x-sqrt     x sqrt ;

mat-sqrt . cr
mat-sqrt  mat sqrt  = . cr                 \ 1
mat-exp   mat exp   = . cr                 \ 1
mat-sin   mat sin   = . cr                 \ 1
mat-round mat round = . cr                 \ 1
dur-neg . cr                               \ -3 s
dur-neg   dur negate = . cr                \ 1
dur-abs . cr                               \ 3 s
x-sqrt . cr                                \ 1.5

\ the store-fused shape ( var op to var ) must agree too
variable out
: mat-sqrt!  mat sqrt to out ;
mat-sqrt!  out  mat sqrt  = . cr           \ 1
: dur-neg!  dur negate to out ;
dur-neg!  out  dur negate  = . cr          \ 1

bye
